Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @dried linguine{180%grams}.

When boiling, add the linguine to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{125%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot,
fry the @Irish Bacon Lardons{100%grams}, mushrooms, garlic and onion until golden,
stirring, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the @chicken stock{1%sachet} to the pan along with the @creme fraiche{125%grams}.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-14%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{}
if the sauce becomes too thick.

Carefully mix in the cooked linguine, @baby spinach{60%grams} and half the
@grated Italian style hard cheese{25%grams}.

Cook until the cheese has melted and the spinach is wilted.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide the creamy bacon linguine between deep plates or #bowls{}.

Top with a sprinkling of chopped chilli (use less if you don't like spice) and
the remaining cheese.

> TIP: If you're cooking for kids you may want to leave out the chilli in this dish!